Step 1: set up ssh key
----------------------

in local terminal, run:
ssh-keygen -o -a 100 -t ed25519 -f ~/.ssh/gitlab_eibie_net_ed25519 -C "gitlab_eibie_net"

add to ~/.ssh/config:
Host gitlab
    Hostname gitlab.eibie.net
    User git
    Port 6622
    IdentityFile ~/.ssh/gitlab_eibie_net_ed25519
    AddressFamily inet

set up public ssh key on gitlab

test ssh:
ssh -T gitlab



Step 2: create python environment
---------------------------------

through conda:
download .requirements_dev.txt
conda create --name dsgamesolver-dev --file .requirements_dev.txt --channel conda-forge -y



Step 3: set up git project
--------------------------

cd existing_folder
git init

git config --local user.name "USERNAME"
git config --local user.email "EMAILADDRESS"

git remote add origin ssh://git@gitlab.eibie.net:6622/steffen/dsgamesolver.git
git config --local core.sshCommand "ssh -o AddressFamily=inet -i ~/.ssh/gitlab_eibie_net_ed25519 -F /dev/null"

git pull



Step 4: set up git hooks
------------------------

pre-commit install-hooks
pre-commit install

pre-commit run



